reviews.review_text: Old Fave.....New Luster Excellent job on a classic.  Well done.  Used to be one of the most played shows in the rotation (well before the commercial release).  Haven't re-visited it in quite some time and ecstatic to have an excuse now.  Fantastic job on the mix; clean, clear and crisp.

Best matrix I've ever heard !!! I posted this as my latest "Bman's Picks" over on reddit because it just struck me so so hard ... Dusborne you are a freaking wizard!!!  and this really is the best matrix I've ever heard and I'm not new to the game so to speak ... This show is spectacular beyond words and it just kicks like a mule from go. The whole 1st set is incredible with ever version keeping this same energy going but then comes the 2nd set !!!  Scarlet>Fires don't get any better than this, different better but not better better ... it's so over the top it defies belief ... from start to finish, every single second builds and builds to massive creative peaks and is the very definition of tension and release ... the Scarlet end jam is 2nd to none and my god the Fire is just un freaking real !!! Everyone is on top of their game and it never falters and just slams and slays the whole 30 minutes ... a killer Estimated keeps this going and the end jam is very jazzy a la 73 jazzy Dead 1983 style. The comes one of my favorite Eyes ever ... it reminds me of tumbling, twisting and twirling ... all in all it's an hour of classic deep dive hard core Grateful Dead and it's an adult portion all day long ... the post space is spectacular as well ... it's a legit 5 star show for me and the matrix gets 5 stars as well ... great job Dusborne and I can't wait for your next because it seems perhaps you've done something different with this one? but whatever you did it's incredible ... Bman1973
